Adebayo Obajemu The Federal Government has launched a central database for the management of recovered assets. The Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami during the launch on Thursday, in Abuja, said all the assets that have been recovered by the Federal Government are now tied to specific projects. The launch was witnessed by officials from government agencies including the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), Independent Corrupt Practices Commission (ICPC), and the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS). In his remark ICPC Chairman, Professor Bolaji Owasanoye said all anti-corruption agencies should be digitized and integrated for easy access. He adds that the idea of the central database system is to ensure that all anti-corruption agencies harmonise all recovered assets